@smolnar82, the typo was there since 269451069f7 (almost 4 years).  Unit tests in `groovy-client` are fine locally without this fix, as well as in [Jenkins](https://builds.apache.org/job/Ambari-trunk-Commit/8804/console).  The same typo is being fixed on trunk in #525 along with httpclient upgrade in `groovy-client`.  Since #538 is also upgrading httpclient and encountering this unit test failure, it seems to me that the failure is due to these upgrades.

@aonishuk @sumitmohanty could you take a look at this PR?

@adoroszlai Setting repository versions is a deprecated feature and I'm sure it's busted in more than 1 place. We shouldn't worry about blueprints yet since a ton of it relies on RepoVersionEntity. I would suggest we merge this change and begin working toward having blueprints switch away from RepoVersionEntity instances.

With that said, the above doesn't seem to be able to cause a StackOverFlow. I just tried a blueprint deployment  and I was able to install a ZK cluster from HDPCore just fine - no overflows.
